A. Data Extraction
	‚Ä¢	Identify and extract from relevant sheets:
	‚Ä¢	Eligible inventory, ineligible inventory, gross BB, advance rate, utilisation, notes outstanding, reserves, days in stock, cash trading margin (CTM), and country mix.
	‚Ä¢	Parse any ‚Äúeligible amount (EUR)‚Äù or ‚Äútotal inventory‚Äù line for CarCo and CarTrade.
	‚Ä¢	Extract ‚ÄúWeighted Avg Days in Inventory‚Äù, ‚ÄúEV Share‚Äù, and ‚ÄúCountry Mix‚Äù if available.

B. Compute Derived Metrics
	‚Ä¢	Overcollateralisation (OC) = (Net BB ‚Äì Notes Outstanding) / Notes Outstanding
	‚Ä¢	Utilisation = Drawn Amount / Total BB
	‚Ä¢	Ageing >300d % = (Value of >300d vehicles) / (Total Inventory)
	‚Ä¢	3M CTM = rolling average from ‚ÄúPurchase Countries Margin‚Äù or Sales data.
	‚Ä¢	Liquidity Coverage = (Reserve Balances / Senior Interest) * Months
	‚Ä¢	Country Concentration = Max(country_value / total_value)
	‚Ä¢	Stress Coverage = (Current margin ‚Äì Applied MVD at Target Rating)

C. Early-Amortisation / Trigger Tests
Create a compliance table:

Trigger	Threshold	Current	Status
3M CTM Floor	‚â• 5.0%	[computed]	‚úÖ/‚ùå
